<p>I have 2 xelement which I want to merge :</p>  <p>The first one is like this :</p>  <pre><code>&lt;element xmlns="test1"&gt;     &lt;child&gt;element child&lt;/child&gt; &lt;/element&gt; </code></pre>  <p>The second one is like  this :</p>  <pre><code>&lt;element2&gt;     &lt;child2&gt;element2 child2&lt;/child2&gt; &lt;/element2&gt; </code></pre>  <p>I would like to obtain the following :</p>  <pre><code>&lt;root xmlns="fusion"&gt;        &lt;element xmlns="test1"&gt;         &lt;child&gt;element child&lt;/child&gt;     &lt;/element&gt;     &lt;element2&gt;         &lt;child2&gt;element2 child2&lt;/child2&gt;     &lt;/element2&gt; &lt;/root&gt;  </code></pre>  <p>The problem is that when I try to merge the 2 xelement in my root node, it automatically add an empty xmlns attribute to my second element which I don't want : </p>  <pre><code>&lt;root xmlns="fusion"&gt;        &lt;element xmlns="test1"&gt;         &lt;child&gt;element child&lt;/child&gt;     &lt;/element&gt;     &lt;element2 xmlns=""&gt;         &lt;child2&gt;element2 child2&lt;/child2&gt;     &lt;/element2&gt; &lt;/root&gt;  </code></pre>  <p>This is my code :</p>  <pre><code>        XNamespace defaultNs = "fusion";         var root = new XElement(defaultNs + "root");          root.Add(element);         root.Add(element2); //when I debug and visualize my element2 I don't have this empty xmlns attribute, it's only when I do the fusion that it appears </code></pre>